{
 "name": "RPlog_Brig_-_Day_Four",
 "title": "Brig: Day Four",
 "summary": "On the fourth day, Lynae Caiton is held in solitude and subjected to a COMPNOR torture regimen of deafening supersonic alarms designed to drive prisoners mad. ISB Director Korynn Fleming, who had counted Lynae a rare friend, watches her unnatural resilience from the control center before entering her cell to interrogate her about Danik Kreldin's plot to seize the throne. Their exchange is heavy with mutual betrayal; Lynae coolly details Kreldin's ambitions and insists the gathering was treasonous talk she would have killed him to stop before allowing open war, while Korynn argues the plot would have plunged the Empire into civil war and ruin. The interrogation ends with Korynn ordering CompForce troopers to beat Lynae into submission with stun batons, then resuming the alarm cycles for twelve more hours. Hours later, a battered Lynae is finally thrown into the larger cell holding Antoine Dareus, who tends to her as best he can. As they recover, the two reset Dareus's repeatedly dislocated shoulder, trade dark fantasies of revenge against Kreldin, share quiet confessions about their families, and confirm that Lynae holds the access codes to Kreldin's Corellian estate before settling down to rest before the next round.",
